    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-26T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.6363/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-26T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Legation’s no. 46 of April 19, noon, and no. 49 of April 25, 6 p.m.<note
                        n="49" xml:id="d475fn49">No. 46, <hi rend="italic">supra;</hi> no. 49, <ref
                            target="#pg_536">p. 536</ref>.</note> An amendment to the Philippine
                    petroleum law was recently passed by the Philippine Legislature. The amendment
                    provides that 61 percent of the stock of a leasing company must be <pb
                        facs="0647" n="551" xml:id="pg_551"/> held by citizens either of the
                    Philippine Islands or of the United States. This measure is not in accord with
                    the provisions for reciprocity contained in the United States general leasing
                    law of February 25, 1920. You are authorized to state positively that the
                    American Government will take steps to secure from the Philippine Legislature at
                    its October session the passage of a law which will be in conformity with the
                    reciprocity provisions of the general leasing law of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
